## Entity and Attribute Descriptions
 
### USER
Represents an application user, either a regular user or an administrator.
 
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `CHAR(36)` | Unique UUID identifier (primary key) |
| `first_name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | User's first name |
| `last_name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | User's last name |
| `email` | `VARCHAR(255)` | Email address (unique) |
| `password` | `VARCHAR(255)` | Password hashed with bcrypt |
| `is_admin` | `BOOLEAN` | Whether the user has admin privileges (default: `false`) |
| `created_at` | `DATETIME` | Record creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | `DATETIME` | Last modification timestamp |
 
---
 
### PLACE
Represents a property listed by a user.
 
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `CHAR(36)` | Unique UUID identifier (primary key) |
| `title` | `VARCHAR(255)` | Title of the place |
| `description` | `TEXT` | Detailed description |
| `price` | `DECIMAL(10,2)` | Price per night |
| `latitude` | `FLOAT` | Geographic latitude (between -90 and 90) |
| `longitude` | `FLOAT` | Geographic longitude (between -180 and 180) |
| `owner_id` | `CHAR(36)` | Reference to the owner (`USER.id`) |
| `created_at` | `DATETIME` | Record creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | `DATETIME` | Last modification timestamp |
 
---
 
### REVIEW
Represents a review left by a user on a place.
 
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `CHAR(36)` | Unique UUID identifier (primary key) |
| `text` | `TEXT` | Review content |
| `rating` | `INT` | Rating given (between 1 and 5) |
| `user_id` | `CHAR(36)` | Reference to the author (`USER.id`) |
| `place_id` | `CHAR(36)` | Reference to the place (`PLACE.id`) |
| `created_at` | `DATETIME` | Record creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | `DATETIME` | Last modification timestamp |
 
---
 
### AMENITY
Represents a feature or service available at a place (e.g. WiFi, swimming pool).
 
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `CHAR(36)` | Unique UUID identifier (primary key) |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | Name of the amenity (unique) |
| `created_at` | `DATETIME` | Record creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | `DATETIME` | Last modification timestamp |
 
---
 
### PLACE_AMENITY
Junction table managing the many-to-many relationship between `PLACE` and `AMENITY`.
 
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `place_id` | `CHAR(36)` | Reference to the place (`PLACE.id`) |
| `amenity_id` | `CHAR(36)` | Reference to the amenity (`AMENITY.id`) |
 
> The primary key is composite: (`place_id`, `amenity_id`).
 
---
 
## Relationships
 
### USER → PLACE (one-to-many)
A user can own multiple places, but each place belongs to exactly one user. The foreign key `owner_id` in `PLACE` references `USER.id`.
 
### USER → REVIEW (one-to-many)
A user can write multiple reviews, but each review is written by exactly one user. The foreign key `user_id` in `REVIEW` references `USER.id`.
 
### PLACE → REVIEW (one-to-many)
A place can receive multiple reviews, but each review is associated with exactly one place. The foreign key `place_id` in `REVIEW` references `PLACE.id`.
 
### PLACE ↔ AMENITY (many-to-many)
A place can offer multiple amenities, and an amenity can be associated with multiple places. This relationship is managed by the `PLACE_AMENITY` junction table.
 
---
 
## Constraints and Business Rules
 
### Database Constraints
 
| Table | Constraint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `USER` | `UNIQUE(email)` | No two users can share the same email address |
| `AMENITY` | `UNIQUE(name)` | No two amenities can share the same name |
| `REVIEW` | `UNIQUE(user_id, place_id)` | A user can only leave one review per place |
| `REVIEW` | `CHECK(rating >= 1 AND rating <= 5)` | Rating must be between 1 and 5 |
| `PLACE` | `CHECK(price > 0)` | Price must be strictly positive |
| `PLACE` | `CHECK(latitude BETWEEN -90 AND 90)` | Valid geographic latitude |
| `PLACE` | `CHECK(longitude BETWEEN -180 AND 180)` | Valid geographic longitude |
| `PLACE_AMENITY` | `PRIMARY KEY(place_id, amenity_id)` | Composite primary key to prevent duplicates |
 
### Application-Level Business Rules
 
- A user **cannot review their own place**.
- A user **cannot leave more than one review** on the same place.
- Only the **owner of a place** can update or delete it (unless the user is an admin).
- Only the **author of a review** can update or delete it (unless the user is an admin).
- An **admin** can create and modify any user, place, review, or amenity without ownership restrictions.
- The **password** is never returned in API responses.
- All `id` fields are **UUID v4** values generated automatically at creation.
- The `created_at` and `updated_at` fields are managed automatically by the `BaseModel`.
